cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SD 

The paper deals with computer vision techniques to detect social interactions in egocentric photo streams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of a Long-Short Term Memory-based Recurrent Neural Network for classification suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves the analysis of temporal data, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of social behavior, which could fall under cs.SD (Social and Information Networks).
